<dataset><identifier system="knb">obfs.224.3</identifier><identifier system="[Costa Rica] La Selva Biological Station">obfs.224.3</identifier><title>Meteorological data at La Selva Biological Station</title><originator><individualName><givenName>Data</givenName><surName>Manager</surName></individualName><address><deliveryPoint>Apartado 676-2050</deliveryPoint><city>San Pedro</city><administrativeArea>San Jose</administrativeArea><postalCode>676-2050</postalCode><country>Costa Rica</country></address><phone>(506) 240-6696</phone><electronicMailAddress>datamgr@ots.ac.cr</electronicMailAddress><role /></originator><originator><individualName><givenName>Data</givenName><surName>Manager</surName></individualName><address><deliveryPoint>Apartado 676-2050</deliveryPoint><city>San Pedro</city><administrativeArea>San Jose</administrativeArea><postalCode>676-2050</postalCode><country>Costa Rica</country></address><phone>(506) 240-6696</phone><electronicMailAddress>datamgr@ots.ac.cr</electronicMailAddress><role>Data Contact</role></originator><originator><individualName><surName>Eric Sanchez</surName></individualName><role>Metadata Provider</role></originator><originator><organizationName>[Costa Rica] La Selva Biological Station</organizationName><role>Originator</role></originator><originator><organizationName>Organization of Biological Field Stations</organizationName><role>Originator</role></originator><abstract><paragraph>La Selva weather data started to be collected in 1957 in a weather station near Casa Rafael. In this site precipitation data was collected manually over a 34-year period. As station operations shifted to the East Bank of the Puerto Viejo River, the meteorological station was moved to the East Bank (the 'Puente' station). Between 1982-1992, both stations were in operation, in 1992 an automatic weather station was installed in Puente site and data collection in Rafael's point ceased. In 1999 long term records were created to join this three data sources: Rafael, manual Puente and automatic Puente.
